      Come on
   =20
 =20

Here is  a story about how the richest person in the world (again!) is anno=
yed that current artificial intelligence companies produce AIs that are too=
 sensitive to humans, so he is starting a rival AI company to produce AIs t=
hat will =E2=80=A6=C2=A0look, it does not actually say =E2=80=9Cmurder us a=
ll=E2=80=9D in the story, but I think you can see=C2=A0where this is headin=
g:

Elon Musk has approached artificial intelligence researchers in recent week=
s about forming a new research lab to develop an alternative to ChatGPT, th=
e high-profile chatbot made by the startup OpenAI, according to two people =
with direct knowledge of the effort and a third person briefed on the conve=
rsations.
In recent months Musk has repeatedly criticized OpenAI for installing safeg=
uards that prevent ChatGPT from producing text that might offend users. Mus=
k, who co-founded OpenAI in 2015 but has since cut ties with the startup, s=
uggested last year that OpenAI=E2=80=99s technology was an example of =E2=
=80=9Ctraining AI to be woke.=E2=80=9D His comments imply that a rival chat=
bot would have fewer restrictions on divisive subjects compared to ChatGPT =
and a related chatbot Microsoft recently launched.
To spearhead the effort, Musk has been recruiting Igor Babuschkin, a resear=
cher who recently left Alphabet=E2=80=99s DeepMind AI unit and specializes =
in the kind of machine-learning models that power chatbots like ChatGPT. In=
 an interview, Babuschkin said building a chatbot with fewer content safegu=
ards is not Musk=E2=80=99s objective.
=E2=80=9CThe goal is to improve the reasoning abilities and the factualness=
 of these language models,=E2=80=9D he said. That includes making sure the =
model=E2=80=99s responses are more trustworthy and reliable, he said.

I mean if you saw a movie and a billionaire character was like =E2=80=9CAI =
today is too nice, we need to make an AI with better reasoning abilities th=
at is not afraid to face facts,=E2=80=9D how would that movie end? Really! =
If the end of human life on earth is an Elon Musk-sponsored AI wiping out h=
umanity while Musk himself hops on a rocket to Mars, will you be surprised?=
 I am looking forward to writing that last week of Money Stuff.=C2=A0=E2=80=
=9CHaving a bit of AI existential angst today,=E2=80=9D Musk  tweeted on Su=
nday, ah.

