<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Tilray</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Maybe a clearer situation is Tilray. Tilray Br=
ands Inc. is a meme-y cannabis company (equity market capitalization $9.6 b=
illion in June 2021, $1.7 billion yesterday) with, naturally, a very retail=
 investor base. Tilray has had some trouble getting shareholders to vote to=
 approve stuff, not because they don=E2=80=99t like the stuff but because t=
hey are retail shareholders and don=E2=80=99t vote. In 2021, it <a href=3D"=
https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30685506.257425/aHR0cHM6Ly93d=
3cuYnVzaW5lc3NpbnNpZGVyLmNvbS9jYW5uYWJpcy1hbWMtbWVtZS1zdG9ja3MtcmV0YWlsLWlu=
dmVzdG9ycy1zaGFyZWhvbGRlcnMtcHJveHktdm90aW5nLTIwMjEtNg/607f07ceef4b8524a319=
a23cB9122bfe7" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_bl=
ank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; ba=
ckground-color: #ccc;"> had trouble</a> getting shareholders to vote to app=
rove a =E2=80=9Ccannabis megamerger.=E2=80=9D Not that they don=E2=80=99t l=
ove a cannabis megamerger, but as Tilray=E2=80=99s CEO said:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">"It's hard to get those shareholde=
rs to show up and vote," Simon said. "You know, nobody has home phones anym=
ore. No one answers their cellphone to an unknown number. When you mail a p=
roxy to someone's house or apartment, it goes in the garbage."</p></blockqu=
ote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Ultimately=C2=A0<a href=3D"https://link.mail.b=
loombergbusiness.com/click/30685506.257425/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9peD9k=
b2M9L0FyY2hpdmVzL2VkZ2FyL2RhdGEvMTczMTM0OC8wMDAxMTQwMzYxMjEwMTU3NTUvbnQxMDA=
yMzkxN3gyXzhrLmh0bQ/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cCcae84d0c" itemprop=3D"StoryLin=
k" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-=
decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color:=
 #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">37.7% of sha=
res voted in favor of the merger</a> and just 0.8% voted against: overwhelm=
ing approval, but not a majority of all the shares. The deal closed anyway,=
 because Tilray did not actually need a majority of all of its shares to ap=
prove the merger.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But Tilray, like AMC, would also like to amend=
 its charter to authorize more shares, and that <em>does=C2=A0</em>require =
a majority.=C2=A0In fact Tilray=C2=A0<em>did=C2=A0</em>get a majority of sh=
ares to <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30685506.2=
57425/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9peD9kb2M9L0FyY2hpdmVzL2VkZ2FyL2RhdGEvMTczM=
TM0OC8wMDAxMTQwMzYxMjEwMzA5MjkvbnkyMDAwMDQwNngxMV84ay5odG0/607f07ceef4b8524=
a319a23cDeab29f9c" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D=
"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-=
bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid=
; background-color: #ccc;">vote to increase its authorized shares</a> in Ju=
ne 2021, but just barely; 227 million of the 449 million shares then outsta=
nding voted yes. (About 33 million voted no.)</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Now it wants to do it again. Now it has about =
615 million shares outstanding, out of about 746.7 million authorized share=
s. Technically these are all its =E2=80=9CClass 2=E2=80=9D shares; its char=
ter authorizes 233 million super-voting =E2=80=9CClass 1=E2=80=9D shares, b=
ut those are no longer outstanding. Tilray would like to amend its charter =
to eliminate the dual class shares and collapse everything into 980 million=
 authorized common shares, which would have two advantages. One is that the=
re=E2=80=99d be neater, better governance, with no super-voting stock and n=
o confusing references to it in the charter. Here=E2=80=99s <a href=3D"http=
s://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/30685506.257425/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc=
2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRhLzE3MzEzNDgvMDAwMTE0MDM2MTIyMDM1NzgwL255=
MjAwMDUzMTF4NF9kZWYxNGEuaHRt/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB1f73c1da" itemprop=3D=
"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #0000=
00; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bott=
om-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> wh=
at Tilray says</a>:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Our Board believes that our Certif=
icate of Incorporation as currently in effect may confuse stockholders, the=
 investing public and other third parties because of references to our Clas=
s 1 common stock. Among other things, eliminating these references will hel=
p to prevent any mistaken belief on the part of the investing public or oth=
ers who report on or follow our publicly-traded equity securities that we m=
ay have another outstanding class of common equity. In addition, the Board =
believes that there should be no Class 1 common shares with supermajority v=
oting rights. Instead, each share of the Company=E2=80=99s common stock sho=
uld have one vote per share.</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The other advantage is, of course, more (regul=
ar) common stock to issue if Tilray needs to.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Inspired by all the other weird preferred stoc=
k deals, Tilray is doing one. It <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusi=
ness.com/click/30685506.257425/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdh=
ci9kYXRhLzE3MzEzNDgvMDAwMTE0MDM2MTIzMDA4MDg4L2JyaGMxMDA0ODY1Ml9kZWZhMTRhLmh=
0bQ/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB62785257" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"=
itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none=
 !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border=
-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> announced last week</a>:</p=
>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Tilray Brands, Inc. (=E2=80=9CTilray Brands=E2=
=80=9D or the =E2=80=9CCompany=E2=80=9D) (NASDAQ | TSX: TLRY), a leading gl=
obal cannabis-lifestyle and consumer packaged goods company, today announce=
d that the Company has entered into an agreement for the issuance of 120,00=
0 shares of Series A Preferred Stock (the =E2=80=9CSeries A Preferred Stock=
=E2=80=9D).</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The Series A Preferred Stock is entitled to 1,=
000 votes per share, but may only vote on the Company=E2=80=99s pending pro=
posal to eliminate Tilray Brand=E2=80=99s Class 1 Common Stock (=E2=80=9CPr=
oposal 3=E2=80=9D). Proposal 3, if approved, would eliminate the unissued C=
lass 1 Common Stock by reclassifying it into shares of the Company=E2=80=99=
s authorized and unissued Class 2 Common Stock.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The Series A Preferred Stock cannot vote indep=
endently, but instead must vote in the same proportion (For or Against) as =
all shares of Class 2 Common Stock are voted. The Series A Preferred Stock =
will convert automatically to Class 2 Common Stock on a one-for-one basis u=
pon the closing of the polls at the Company=E2=80=99s adjourned annual meet=
ing of stockholders. Upon conversion, there will be no meaningful dilution =
impact to Class 2 shareholders from the Series A Preferred Stock, as diluti=
on will be limited to only 0.0002%.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CWe believe the issuance of the Series=
 A Preferred Stock will help amplify and safeguard the rights of all stockh=
olders through the approval of our proposed Charter Amendment. =C2=A0This w=
ould ultimately help execute our strategic plan by facilitating accretive a=
cquisitions,=E2=80=9D commented Irwin D. Simon, Tilray Brands=E2=80=99 Chai=
rman and Chief Executive Officer. =C2=A0=E2=80=9CAn overwhelming majority o=
f our stockholders that have voted at our annual meeting have voted in favo=
r of the Charter Amendment (Proposal 3), but due to the nature of our stock=
holder base, the proposal to amend our Charter does not yet have enough vot=
es to pass,=E2=80=9D Mr. Simon continued. =E2=80=9CThe Series A Preferred S=
tock has been structured to protect stockholder interests and is an importa=
nt part of our efforts to simplify the Company=E2=80=99s capital structure =
and modernize our corporate governance with our proposed Charter Amendment.=
=E2=80=9D</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusi=
ness.com/click/30685506.257425/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9peD9kb2M9L0FyY2hp=
dmVzL2VkZ2FyL2RhdGEvMTczMTM0OC8wMDAxMTQwMzYxMjMwMDc3MzYvbnkyMDAwNzY2M3gyXzh=
rLmh0bQ/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cE4542fb6b" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=
=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: =
none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; bo=
rder-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> buyer of the preferred =
stock</a> is called Double Diamond Holdings Ltd. Basically the idea is that=
 Tilray will give one friendly holder an extra 120 million votes, probably =
enough to pass the charter amendment, and then when the vote is done that f=
riendly holder=E2=80=99s super-voting shares will poof into a smallish numb=
er of regular shares. Meanwhile the friendly holder will vote exactly the s=
ame way as the actual common shareholders =E2=80=94=C2=A0it=E2=80=99s just =
that the friendly holder will vote all its shares, while the common shareho=
lders won=E2=80=99t. If 45% of the common votes yes and 5% votes no,=C2=A0t=
hen 90% of the super-voting shares will vote yes, which will help. Tilray i=
s issuing super-voting stock, briefly, in order to get rid of its super-vot=
ing stock.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This is basically Outcome 3 in my AMC scenario=
s: If the Tilray shareholders who bother to vote vote yes, then the proposa=
l will pass, despite not getting a majority of the outstanding common share=
s. Delaware law requires a majority of all common shares to vote to approve=
 a charter amendment, and Tilray =E2=80=94=C2=A0like AMC =E2=80=94=C2=A0has=
 just opted out of that requirement with a weird trick. In AMC that=E2=80=
=99s controversial among the shareholders; in Tilray I expect it won=E2=80=
=99t be. (Again, they keep voting in favor of this stuff, to the extent the=
y vote.) I=E2=80=99m not=C2=A0<em>sure=C2=A0</em>that means it=E2=80=99s le=
gal =E2=80=94=C2=A0perhaps Delaware law means what it says, that you need a=
 majority of all shares to approve a charter amendment, and this sort of gi=
mmick is too cute? =E2=80=94=C2=A0but I=E2=80=99m not sure who would object=
.</p>
